37// Type: identifying the types of the display names.
38//
39// ecma402/#sec-properties-of-intl-displaynames-instances
40enum class Type {
41 kUndefined,
42 kLanguage,
43 kRegion,
44 kScript,
45 kCurrency,
46 kCalendar,
47 kDateTimeField
48};
49
50bool IsUnicodeScriptSubtag(const std::string& value) {
51 UErrorCode status = U_ZERO_ERROR;
52 icu::LocaleBuilder builder;
53 builder.setScript(value).build(status);
54 return U_SUCCESS(status);
55}
56
57bool IsUnicodeRegionSubtag(const std::string& value) {
58 if (value.empty()) return false;
59 UErrorCode status = U_ZERO_ERROR;
60 icu::LocaleBuilder builder;
61 builder.setRegion(value).build(status);
62 return U_SUCCESS(status);
63}
64
65UDisplayContext ToUDisplayContext(JSDisplayNames::Style style) {
66 switch (style) {
67 case JSDisplayNames::Style::kLong:
68 return UDISPCTX_LENGTH_FULL;
69 case JSDisplayNames::Style::kShort:
70 case JSDisplayNames::Style::kNarrow:
71 return UDISPCTX_LENGTH_SHORT;
72 }
73}

77// Abstract class for all different types.
78class DisplayNamesInternal {
79 public:
80 static constexpr ExternalPointerTag kManagedTag = kDisplayNamesInternalTag;
81
82 DisplayNamesInternal() = default;
83 virtual ~DisplayNamesInternal() = default;
84 virtual const char* type() const = 0;
85 virtual icu::Locale locale() const = 0;
86 virtual Maybe<icu::UnicodeString> of(Isolate* isolate,
87 const char* code) const = 0;
88};

92class LocaleDisplayNamesCommon : public DisplayNamesInternal {
93 public:
94 LocaleDisplayNamesCommon(const icu::Locale& locale,
95 JSDisplayNames::Style style, bool fallback,
96 bool dialect)
97 : style_(style) {
98 UDisplayContext sub =
99 fallback ? UDISPCTX_SUBSTITUTE : UDISPCTX_NO_SUBSTITUTE;
100 UDisplayContext dialect_context =
101 dialect ? UDISPCTX_DIALECT_NAMES : UDISPCTX_STANDARD_NAMES;
102 UDisplayContext display_context[] = {ToUDisplayContext(style_),
103 dialect_context,
104 UDISPCTX_CAPITALIZATION_NONE, sub};
105 ldn_.reset(
106 icu::LocaleDisplayNames::createInstance(locale, display_context, 4));
107 }
108
109 ~LocaleDisplayNamesCommon() override = default;
110
111 icu::Locale locale() const override { return ldn_->getLocale(); }
112
113 protected:
114 icu::LocaleDisplayNames* locale_display_names() const { return ldn_.get(); }
115
116 private:
117 std::unique_ptr<icu::LocaleDisplayNames> ldn_;
118 JSDisplayNames::Style style_;
119};
120
121class LanguageNames : public LocaleDisplayNamesCommon {
122 public:
123 LanguageNames(const icu::Locale& locale, JSDisplayNames::Style style,
124 bool fallback, bool dialect)
125 : LocaleDisplayNamesCommon(locale, style, fallback, dialect) {}
126
127 ~LanguageNames() override = default;
128
129 const char* type() const override { return "language"; }
130
131 Maybe<icu::UnicodeString> of(Isolate* isolate,
132 const char* code) const override {
133 UErrorCode status = U_ZERO_ERROR;
134 // 1.a If code does not match the unicode_language_id production, throw a
135 // RangeError exception.
136 icu::Locale tagLocale = icu::Locale::forLanguageTag(code, status);
137 icu::Locale l(tagLocale.getBaseName());
138 if (U_FAILURE(status) || tagLocale != l ||
139 !JSLocale::StartsWithUnicodeLanguageId(code)) {
140 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(
141 isolate, NewRangeError(MessageTemplate::kInvalidArgument),
142 Nothing<icu::UnicodeString>());
143 }
144
145 // 1.b If IsStructurallyValidLanguageTag(code) is false, throw a RangeError
146 // exception.
147
148 // 1.c Set code to CanonicalizeUnicodeLocaleId(code).
149 l.canonicalize(status);
150 std::string checked = l.toLanguageTag<std::string>(status);
151
152 if (U_FAILURE(status)) {
153 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(
154 isolate, NewRangeError(MessageTemplate::kInvalidArgument),
155 Nothing<icu::UnicodeString>());
156 }
157
158 icu::UnicodeString result;
159 locale_display_names()->localeDisplayName(checked.c_str(), result);
160
161 return Just(result);
162 }
163};
164
165class RegionNames : public LocaleDisplayNamesCommon {
166 public:
167 RegionNames(const icu::Locale& locale, JSDisplayNames::Style style,
168 bool fallback, bool dialect)
169 : LocaleDisplayNamesCommon(locale, style, fallback, dialect) {}
170
171 ~RegionNames() override = default;
172
173 const char* type() const override { return "region"; }
174
175 Maybe<icu::UnicodeString> of(Isolate* isolate,
176 const char* code) const override {
177 std::string code_str(code);
178 if (!IsUnicodeRegionSubtag(code_str)) {
179 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(
180 isolate, NewRangeError(MessageTemplate::kInvalidArgument),
181 Nothing<icu::UnicodeString>());
182 }
183
184 icu::UnicodeString result;
185 locale_display_names()->regionDisplayName(code_str.c_str(), result);
186 return Just(result);
187 }
188};

190class ScriptNames : public LocaleDisplayNamesCommon {
191 public:
192 ScriptNames(const icu::Locale& locale, JSDisplayNames::Style style,
193 bool fallback, bool dialect)
194 : LocaleDisplayNamesCommon(locale, style, fallback, dialect) {}
195
196 ~ScriptNames() override = default;

200 Maybe<icu::UnicodeString> of(Isolate* isolate,

207 }
208
209 icu::UnicodeString result;
210 locale_display_names()->scriptDisplayName(code_str.c_str(), result);
211 return Just(result);
212 }

214
215class KeyValueDisplayNames : public LocaleDisplayNamesCommon {
216 public:
217 KeyValueDisplayNames(const icu::Locale& locale, JSDisplayNames::Style style,
218 bool fallback, bool dialect, const char* key,
219 bool prevent_fallback)
220 : LocaleDisplayNamesCommon(locale, style, fallback, dialect),
221 key_(key),
222 prevent_fallback_(prevent_fallback) {}
223
224 ~KeyValueDisplayNames() override = default;
225
226 const char* type() const override { return key_.c_str(); }
227
228 Maybe<icu::UnicodeString> of(Isolate* isolate,
229 const char* code) const override {
230 std::string code_str(code);
231 icu::UnicodeString result;
232 locale_display_names()->keyValueDisplayName(key_.c_str(), code_str.c_str(),
233 result);
234 // Work around the issue that the keyValueDisplayNames ignore no
235 // substituion and always fallback.
236 if (prevent_fallback_ && (result.length() == 3) &&
237 (code_str.length() == 3) &&
238 (result == icu::UnicodeString(code_str.c_str(), -1, US_INV))) {
239 result.setToBogus();
240 }
241
242 return Just(result);
243 }
244
245 private:
246 std::string key_;
247 bool prevent_fallback_;
248};
249
250class CurrencyNames : public KeyValueDisplayNames {
251 public:
252 CurrencyNames(const icu::Locale& locale, JSDisplayNames::Style style,
253 bool fallback, bool dialect)
254 : KeyValueDisplayNames(locale, style, fallback, dialect, "currency",
255 fallback == false) {}
256
257 ~CurrencyNames() override = default;
258
259 Maybe<icu::UnicodeString> of(Isolate* isolate,
260 const char* code) const override {
261 std::string code_str(code);
262 if (!Intl::IsWellFormedCurrency(code_str)) {
263 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(
264 isolate, NewRangeError(MessageTemplate::kInvalidArgument),
265 Nothing<icu::UnicodeString>());
266 }
267 return KeyValueDisplayNames::of(isolate, code);
268 }
269};

271class CalendarNames : public KeyValueDisplayNames {
272 public:
273 CalendarNames(const icu::Locale& locale, JSDisplayNames::Style style,
274 bool fallback, bool dialect)
275 : KeyValueDisplayNames(locale, style, fallback, dialect, "calendar",
276 false) {}
277
278 ~CalendarNames() override = default;
279
280 Maybe<icu::UnicodeString> of(Isolate* isolate,
281 const char* code) const override {
282 std::string code_str(code);
283 if (!Intl::IsWellFormedCalendar(code_str)) {
284 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(
285 isolate, NewRangeError(MessageTemplate::kInvalidArgument),
286 Nothing<icu::UnicodeString>());
287 }
288 return KeyValueDisplayNames::of(isolate, strcmp(code, "gregory") == 0
289 ? "gregorian"
290 : strcmp(code, "ethioaa") == 0
291 ? "ethiopic-amete-alem"
292 : code);
293 }
294};

296UDateTimePGDisplayWidth StyleToUDateTimePGDisplayWidth(
297 JSDisplayNames::Style style) {
298 switch (style) {
299 case JSDisplayNames::Style::kLong:
300 return UDATPG_WIDE;
301 case JSDisplayNames::Style::kShort:
302 return UDATPG_ABBREVIATED;
303 case JSDisplayNames::Style::kNarrow:
304 return UDATPG_NARROW;
305 }
306}
307
308UDateTimePatternField StringToUDateTimePatternField(const char* code) {
309 switch (code[0]) {
310 case 'd':
311 if (strcmp(code, "day") == 0) return UDATPG_DAY_FIELD;
312 if (strcmp(code, "dayPeriod") == 0) return UDATPG_DAYPERIOD_FIELD;
313 break;
314 case 'e':
315 if (strcmp(code, "era") == 0) return UDATPG_ERA_FIELD;
316 break;
317 case 'h':
318 if (strcmp(code, "hour") == 0) return UDATPG_HOUR_FIELD;
319 break;
320 case 'm':
321 if (strcmp(code, "minute") == 0) return UDATPG_MINUTE_FIELD;
322 if (strcmp(code, "month") == 0) return UDATPG_MONTH_FIELD;
323 break;
324 case 'q':
325 if (strcmp(code, "quarter") == 0) return UDATPG_QUARTER_FIELD;
326 break;
327 case 's':
328 if (strcmp(code, "second") == 0) return UDATPG_SECOND_FIELD;
329 break;
330 case 't':
331 if (strcmp(code, "timeZoneName") == 0) return UDATPG_ZONE_FIELD;
332 break;
333 case 'w':
334 if (strcmp(code, "weekOfYear") == 0) return UDATPG_WEEK_OF_YEAR_FIELD;
335 if (strcmp(code, "weekday") == 0) return UDATPG_WEEKDAY_FIELD;
336 break;
337 case 'y':
338 if (strcmp(code, "year") == 0) return UDATPG_YEAR_FIELD;
339 break;
340 default:
341 break;
342 }
343 return UDATPG_FIELD_COUNT;
344}
345
346class DateTimeFieldNames : public DisplayNamesInternal {
347 public:
348 DateTimeFieldNames(const icu::Locale& locale, JSDisplayNames::Style style,
349 bool fallback)
350 : locale_(locale), width_(StyleToUDateTimePGDisplayWidth(style)) {
351 UErrorCode status = U_ZERO_ERROR;
352 generator_.reset(
353 icu::DateTimePatternGenerator::createInstance(locale_, status));
354 DCHECK(U_SUCCESS(status));
355 }
356
357 ~DateTimeFieldNames() override = default;
358
359 const char* type() const override { return "dateTimeField"; }
360
361 icu::Locale locale() const override { return locale_; }
362
363 Maybe<icu::UnicodeString> of(Isolate* isolate,
364 const char* code) const override {
365 UDateTimePatternField field = StringToUDateTimePatternField(code);
366 if (field == UDATPG_FIELD_COUNT) {
367 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(
368 isolate, NewRangeError(MessageTemplate::kInvalidArgument),
369 Nothing<icu::UnicodeString>());
370 }
371 return Just(generator_->getFieldDisplayName(field, width_));
372 }
373
374 private:
375 icu::Locale locale_;
376 UDateTimePGDisplayWidth width_;
377 std::unique_ptr<icu::DateTimePatternGenerator> generator_;
378};
379
380DisplayNamesInternal* CreateInternal(const icu::Locale& locale,
381 JSDisplayNames::Style style, Type type,
382 bool fallback, bool dialect) {
383 switch (type) {
384 case Type::kLanguage:
385 return new LanguageNames(locale, style, fallback, dialect);
386 case Type::kRegion:
387 return new RegionNames(locale, style, fallback, false);
388 case Type::kScript:
389 return new ScriptNames(locale, style, fallback, false);
390 case Type::kCurrency:
391 return new CurrencyNames(locale, style, fallback, false);
392 case Type::kCalendar:
393 return new CalendarNames(locale, style, fallback, false);
394 case Type::kDateTimeField:
395 return new DateTimeFieldNames(locale, style, fallback);
396 default:
397 UNREACHABLE();
398 }
399}

403// ecma402 #sec-Intl.DisplayNames
404MaybeHandle<JSDisplayNames> JSDisplayNames::New(Isolate* isolate,
405 Handle<Map> map,
406 Handle<Object> locales,
407 Handle<Object> input_options) {
408 const char* service = "Intl.DisplayNames";
409 Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
410
411 Handle<JSReceiver> options;
412 // 3. Let requestedLocales be ? CanonicalizeLocaleList(locales).
413 Maybe<std::vector<std::string>> maybe_requested_locales =
414 Intl::CanonicalizeLocaleList(isolate, locales);
415 MAYBE_RETURN(maybe_requested_locales, Handle<JSDisplayNames>());
416 std::vector<std::string> requested_locales =
417 maybe_requested_locales.FromJust();
418
419 // 4. Let options be ? GetOptionsObject(options).
420 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, options,
421 GetOptionsObject(isolate, input_options, service),
422 JSDisplayNames);
423
424 // Note: No need to create a record. It's not observable.
425 // 5. Let opt be a new Record.
426
427 // 6. Let localeData be %DisplayNames%.[[LocaleData]].
428
429 // 7. Let matcher be ? GetOption(options, "localeMatcher", "string", «
430 // "lookup", "best fit" », "best fit").
431 Maybe<Intl::MatcherOption> maybe_locale_matcher =
432 Intl::GetLocaleMatcher(isolate, options, service);
433 MAYBE_RETURN(maybe_locale_matcher, MaybeHandle<JSDisplayNames>());
434
435 // 8. Set opt.[[localeMatcher]] to matcher.
436 Intl::MatcherOption matcher = maybe_locale_matcher.FromJust();
437
438 // ecma402/#sec-Intl.DisplayNames-internal-slots
439 // The value of the [[RelevantExtensionKeys]] internal slot is
440 // « ».
441 std::set<std::string> relevant_extension_keys = {};
442 // 9. Let r be ResolveLocale(%DisplayNames%.[[AvailableLocales]],
443 // requestedLocales, opt, %DisplayNames%.[[RelevantExtensionKeys]]).
444 Maybe<Intl::ResolvedLocale> maybe_resolve_locale =
445 Intl::ResolveLocale(isolate, JSDisplayNames::GetAvailableLocales(),
446 requested_locales, matcher, relevant_extension_keys);
447 if (maybe_resolve_locale.IsNothing()) {
448 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NewRangeError(MessageTemplate::kIcuError),
449 JSDisplayNames);
450 }
451 Intl::ResolvedLocale r = maybe_resolve_locale.FromJust();
452
453 icu::Locale icu_locale = r.icu_locale;
454
455 // 10. Let s be ? GetOption(options, "style", "string",
456 // «"long", "short", "narrow"», "long").
457 Maybe<Style> maybe_style = GetStringOption<Style>(
458 isolate, options, "style", service, {"long", "short", "narrow"},
459 {Style::kLong, Style::kShort, Style::kNarrow}, Style::kLong);
460 MAYBE_RETURN(maybe_style, MaybeHandle<JSDisplayNames>());
461 Style style_enum = maybe_style.FromJust();
462
463 // 11. Set displayNames.[[Style]] to style.
464
465 // 12. Let type be ? GetOption(options, "type", "string", « "language",
466 // "region", "script", "currency" , "calendar", "dateTimeField", "unit"»,
467 // undefined).
468 Maybe<Type> maybe_type = GetStringOption<Type>(
469 isolate, options, "type", service,
470 {"language", "region", "script", "currency", "calendar", "dateTimeField"},
471 {Type::kLanguage, Type::kRegion, Type::kScript, Type::kCurrency,
472 Type::kCalendar, Type::kDateTimeField},
473 Type::kUndefined);
474 MAYBE_RETURN(maybe_type, MaybeHandle<JSDisplayNames>());
475 Type type_enum = maybe_type.FromJust();
476
477 // 13. If type is undefined, throw a TypeError exception.
478 if (type_enum == Type::kUndefined) {
479 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kInvalidArgument),
480 JSDisplayNames);
481 }
482
483 // 14. Set displayNames.[[Type]] to type.
484
485 // 15. Let fallback be ? GetOption(options, "fallback", "string",
486 // « "code", "none" », "code").
487 Maybe<Fallback> maybe_fallback = GetStringOption<Fallback>(
488 isolate, options, "fallback", service, {"code", "none"},
489 {Fallback::kCode, Fallback::kNone}, Fallback::kCode);
490 MAYBE_RETURN(maybe_fallback, MaybeHandle<JSDisplayNames>());
491 Fallback fallback_enum = maybe_fallback.FromJust();
492
493 // 16. Set displayNames.[[Fallback]] to fallback.
494
495 LanguageDisplay language_display_enum = LanguageDisplay::kDialect;
496 // 24. Let languageDisplay be ? GetOption(options, "languageDisplay",
497 // "string", « "dialect", "standard" », "dialect").
498 Maybe<LanguageDisplay> maybe_language_display =
499 GetStringOption<LanguageDisplay>(
500 isolate, options, "languageDisplay", service, {"dialect", "standard"},
501 {LanguageDisplay::kDialect, LanguageDisplay::kStandard},
502 LanguageDisplay::kDialect);
503 MAYBE_RETURN(maybe_language_display, MaybeHandle<JSDisplayNames>());
504 // 25. If type is "language", then
505 if (type_enum == Type::kLanguage) {
506 // a. Set displayNames.[[LanguageDisplay]] to languageDisplay.
507 language_display_enum = maybe_language_display.FromJust();
508 }
509
510 // Set displayNames.[[Fallback]] to fallback.
511
512 // 17. Set displayNames.[[Locale]] to the value of r.[[Locale]].
513
514 // Let dataLocale be r.[[dataLocale]].
515
516 // Let dataLocaleData be localeData.[[<dataLocale>]].
517
518 // Let types be dataLocaleData.[[types]].
519
520 // Assert: types is a Record (see 1.3.3).
521
522 // Let typeFields be types.[[<type>]].
523
524 // Assert: typeFields is a Record (see 1.3.3).
525
526 // Let styleFields be typeFields.[[<style>]].
527
528 // Assert: styleFields is a Record (see 1.3.3).
529
530 // Set displayNames.[[Fields]] to styleFields.
531
532 DisplayNamesInternal* internal = CreateInternal(
533 icu_locale, style_enum, type_enum, fallback_enum == Fallback::kCode,
534 language_display_enum == LanguageDisplay::kDialect);
535 if (internal == nullptr) {
536 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kIcuError),
537 JSDisplayNames);
538 }
539
540 Handle<Managed<DisplayNamesInternal>> managed_internal =
541 Managed<DisplayNamesInternal>::FromRawPtr(isolate, 0, internal);
542
543 Handle<JSDisplayNames> display_names =
544 Handle<JSDisplayNames>::cast(factory->NewFastOrSlowJSObjectFromMap(map));
545 display_names->set_flags(0);
546 display_names->set_style(style_enum);
547 display_names->set_fallback(fallback_enum);
548 display_names->set_language_display(language_display_enum);
549
550 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
551 display_names->set_internal(*managed_internal);
552
553 // Return displayNames.
554 return display_names;
555}

557// ecma402 #sec-Intl.DisplayNames.prototype.resolvedOptions
558Handle<JSObject> JSDisplayNames::ResolvedOptions(
559 Isolate* isolate, Handle<JSDisplayNames> display_names) {
560 Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
561 // 4. Let options be ! ObjectCreate(%ObjectPrototype%).
562 Handle<JSObject> options = factory->NewJSObject(isolate->object_function());
563
564 DisplayNamesInternal* internal = display_names->internal()->raw();
565
566 Maybe<std::string> maybe_locale = Intl::ToLanguageTag(internal->locale());
567 DCHECK(maybe_locale.IsJust());
568 Handle<String> locale = isolate->factory()->NewStringFromAsciiChecked(
569 maybe_locale.FromJust().c_str());
570 Handle<String> style = display_names->StyleAsString();
571 Handle<String> type = factory->NewStringFromAsciiChecked(internal->type());
572 Handle<String> fallback = display_names->FallbackAsString();
573 Handle<String> language_display = display_names->LanguageDisplayAsString();
574
575 Maybe<bool> maybe_create_locale = JSReceiver::CreateDataProperty(
576 isolate, options, factory->locale_string(), locale, Just(kDontThrow));
577 DCHECK(maybe_create_locale.FromJust());
578 USE(maybe_create_locale);
579
580 Maybe<bool> maybe_create_style = JSReceiver::CreateDataProperty(
581 isolate, options, factory->style_string(), style, Just(kDontThrow));
582 DCHECK(maybe_create_style.FromJust());
583 USE(maybe_create_style);
584
585 Maybe<bool> maybe_create_type = JSReceiver::CreateDataProperty(
586 isolate, options, factory->type_string(), type, Just(kDontThrow));
587 DCHECK(maybe_create_type.FromJust());
588 USE(maybe_create_type);
589
590 Maybe<bool> maybe_create_fallback = JSReceiver::CreateDataProperty(
591 isolate, options, factory->fallback_string(), fallback, Just(kDontThrow));
592 DCHECK(maybe_create_fallback.FromJust());
593 USE(maybe_create_fallback);
594
595 if (std::strcmp("language", internal->type()) == 0) {
596 Maybe<bool> maybe_create_language_display =
597 JSReceiver::CreateDataProperty(isolate, options,
598 factory->languageDisplay_string(),
599 language_display, Just(kDontThrow));
600 DCHECK(maybe_create_language_display.FromJust());
601 USE(maybe_create_language_display);
602 }
603
604 return options;
605}

607// ecma402 #sec-Intl.DisplayNames.prototype.of
608MaybeHandle<Object> JSDisplayNames::Of(Isolate* isolate,
609 Handle<JSDisplayNames> display_names,
610 Handle<Object> code_obj) {
611 Handle<String> code;
612 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, code, Object::ToString(isolate, code_obj),
613 Object);
614 DisplayNamesInternal* internal = display_names->internal()->raw();
615 Maybe<icu::UnicodeString> maybe_result =
616 internal->of(isolate, code->ToCString().get());
617 MAYBE_RETURN(maybe_result, Handle<Object>());
618 icu::UnicodeString result = maybe_result.FromJust();
619 if (result.isBogus()) {
620 return isolate->factory()->undefined_value();
621 }
622 return Intl::ToString(isolate, result).ToHandleChecked();
623}

640Handle<String> JSDisplayNames::StyleAsString() const {
641 switch (style()) {
642 case Style::kLong:
643 return GetReadOnlyRoots().long_string_handle();
644 case Style::kShort:
645 return GetReadOnlyRoots().short_string_handle();
646 case Style::kNarrow:
647 return GetReadOnlyRoots().narrow_string_handle();
648 }
649 UNREACHABLE();
650}
651
652Handle<String> JSDisplayNames::FallbackAsString() const {
653 switch (fallback()) {
654 case Fallback::kCode:
655 return GetReadOnlyRoots().code_string_handle();
656 case Fallback::kNone:
657 return GetReadOnlyRoots().none_string_handle();
658 }
659 UNREACHABLE();
660}
661
662Handle<String> JSDisplayNames::LanguageDisplayAsString() const {
663 switch (language_display()) {
664 case LanguageDisplay::kDialect:
665 return GetReadOnlyRoots().dialect_string_handle();
666 case LanguageDisplay::kStandard:
667 return GetReadOnlyRoots().standard_string_handle();
668 }
669 UNREACHABLE();
670}
